		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Electromyography</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Electromyography</b> (EMG) is a technique for evaluating and recording the activation signal of muscles. EMG is performed using an <a href="/wiki/Medical_instrument" title="Medical instrument" class="mw-redirect">instrument</a> called an <b>electromyograph</b>, to produce a record called an <b>electromyogram</b>. An electromyograph detects the <a href="/wiki/Electrical_potential" title="Electrical potential" class="mw-redirect">electrical potential</a> generated by muscle <a href="/wiki/Cell_(biology)" title="Cell (biology)">cells</a> when these cells <a href="/wiki/Muscle_contraction" title="Muscle contraction">contract</a>, and also when the cells are at rest.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
<tr>
<td>
